{{Internet hosting}}
'''Peer-to-peer web hosting''' is using [[peer-to-peer]] networking to distribute access to [[webpage]]s.<ref>{{cite web|title=Peer-To-Peer File Sharing|url=http://www.activewebhosting.com/faq/legal-p2p.html|publisher=Active Web Hosting|accessdate=3 November 2013}}</ref>  This is differentiated from the [[client–server model]] which involves the distribution of Web data between dedicated [[web server]]s and user-end client computers. P2P web hosting may take the form of P2P [[web cache]]s and [[content delivery network]]s like [[Dijjer]] and [[Coral Cache]] which allow users to hold copies of data from single web pages and distribute the caches with other users for faster access during peak traffic.{{citation needed|date=July 2014}}

